Comment: Saw this yesterday with my dad at Imax as a gift for his birthday. This movie is worth every penny! The storyline, narrative, film making and visual are fantastic. I have to say this was incredibly brave to do and without giving anything away, this trailer does a brilliant job at keeping it all secretive without spoiling it. It's a type of movie that requires a lot of attention and listening. The script writing is done very cleverly and actually gets away with what they are tackling. The stunts with the music is truly an experience worth having. It does feel different to the past few movies, and I would liken it to feeling more closely related to MI3, but the comedy saves it from getting overwhelming.

author: @brakmaster
Movie Name: Mission - Impossible - Dead Reckoning Part One

Comment:
The movie is 1 year old!!!

This movie acts as a timely rumination on the dangers of AI; it shouldn’t come as a surprise since modern technology could potentially replace human beings making more calculating decisions to make the world more stable
In this case calculating the position of a moving object
Definitely one of the franchises best installments!
Long but intriguing given an uneasy feeling of this tech evolving, learning, and exploiting a human’s weakness
This makes Ethan and his team rely more on paranoia than their training and instincts 
Tom Cruise still has it, love they brought back supporting players from older films like Vanessa Kirby and Rebecca Ferguson
I really liked Hayley Atwell a lot, she has so much charm unsure what to make of her situation going her own way but staying alive in the process
Action and stunts still deliver too pushing them even further and higher
I’m glad this cliffhanger didn't end on a too somber note, really wondering now how they will wrap up everything with part 2
Much needed humor adds to the variety of the various stuff the characters get into
You’re either on board with the set up or just finding it far too silly being full of plot holes
Maybe too much exposition and some empty dialogue with weak villains but fun and definitely worth the wait
Cruise and company still bring all the intensity in a saga that manages to not overstay its welcome

author: @daveo6277
Movie Name: Mission - Impossible - Dead Reckoning Part One

Comment:
@brunoheggli2888  That’s like saying a drama just has silly dialogue scenes. It is, ironically, quite a silly comment.

Also at this point I’m watching the Mission movies for the characters just as much as the action- unlike so many other action franchises the Mission characters have genuine depth, and range from likeable and funny to fascinating and sinister. Ethan Hunt has grown from a somewhat nondescript hero into a convincing, compelling character whose conflict of interest is intriguing, and continues to be explored. Luther is such a commanding, consistent presence within the films. Isla is a complex, three-dimensional character (perhaps the first female character  
in the franchise who can be described as such). And Simon Pegg is just so much fun, how can you not love him. This is without mentioning new editions, returning favourites and the wonderfully chilling Solomon Lane. I find the plots to be engaging and sometimes quite clever (particularly in the case of Rouge Nation and Fallout). 

It’s fine if you don’t enjoy the movies, but to reduce them- the recent ones especially- to nothing more than silly stunts is reductive,  and quite frankly very small-minded of you.
